COVID-19 virus JOHANNESBURG - The Department of Health has confirmed to eNCA on Wednesday that South Africa has recorded more than 17,700 new COVID-19 infections in the last 24 hours. READ: COVID-19 in SA: When can we expect the vaccine? This is the highest number of daily COVID-19 cases recorded since the beginning of the pandemic. The Department of Health stated 17,710 new cases of the coronavirus have been reported, with a positivity rate of 33 percent. "The positivity rate, being an indicator of the rapidity of the spread, remains of major concern," Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize said in a statement. 465 people have died of COVID-19 since the last report.  As of today, the total number of confirmed #COVID19 cases is 1 039 161, the total number of deaths is 28 033 and the total number of recoveries is 867 597. pic.twitter.com/e6UIG9vTik